-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Oct 22
-- 
-- Wed Oct 22, 2014 01:49AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Oct 22 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Wednesday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- The interim government proposed a gradual increase of the retirement age to 65 years for both women and men and increase of social contributions by 1 percentage points a year in the next for as a measure to decrease gaping shortfalls in the country's pension system. (Capital Daily, Monitor, 24 Chasa, Trud, Sega, Presa) -- The Socialists are ready to hold talks with centre-right GERB party to seek joint positions, its leader said. (Monitor, 24 Chasa, Capital Daily, Sega, Presa, Standart, Trud) -- The leaders of GERB party and the Reformist Bloc met late on Tuesday and moved closer to reaching an agreement to form a government with a possible third partner - the nationalist Patriotic Front. (Presa, Trud, 24 Chasa) -- A newly established investment firm Gemcorp Capital has expressed interest to join the Austrian consultancy EPIC and an Omani sovereign wealth fund and work for the rescue of troubled Corporate Commercial Bank <6C9.BB>, a letter sent to the finance ministry and the government said. (24 Chasa, Presa, Standart, Trud)